The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Indian Hotels profit zooms to Rs 106 cr

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, June 6: Indian Hotels Company Limited has posted a profit after tax of Rs 106 crore in 2004-05, an increase of 74 per cent from Rs 61 crore in the previous fiscal.

 The total revenue of the company increased 26 per cent from Rs 694 crore to Rs 873 crore. The board has recommended a 100 per cent dividend.

 The gross profit of the company is Rs 207 crore compared with Rs 128 crore in the previous year, an increase of 62 per cent. The companys profit before tax grew 78 per cent to Rs 142 crore from previous years Rs 80 crore.

 Indian Hotels Company managing director Raymond N. Bickson said, The growth was driven by a healthy improvement in average room rates because of heavy tourist traffic in most locations, backed by steady growth in our food and beverage business.

 In the fourth quarter of the financial year ended March 31, the company has registered an increase of 13.5 per cent in net profit to Rs 42 crore from Rs 37 crore in the corresponding period last fiscal.

 However, the gross profit of the company increased 61 per cent to Rs 74 crore from Rs 46 crore in the year-ago period.

 The total revenue of the company increased 22 per cent to Rs 270 crore from Rs 221 crore in the year-ago period.

 The consolidated revenue of the company, including subsidiaries, joint ventures and associates, increased 30 per cent at Rs 1,365 crore compared with Rs 1,046 crore achieved during the previous year.

 Consolidate gross profit for the fiscal grew 73 per cent from Rs 222 crore in the previous year to Rs 385 crore. Also, the consolidated profit after tax increased 81 per cent from the previous years Rs 72 crore to Rs 130 crore.

 In March 2004, the company had raised $150 million by issuing foreign currency convertible bonds.




